goals.question: What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of ages in the dataset and identify any potential outliers.

goals.question: What is the average height of people in the dataset?
goals.rationale: A box plot will help us identify the median height, as well as any outliers or skewness in the data.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between age and height in the dataset?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of age and height

goals.question: What are the most common names in the dataset?
goals.rationale: A bar chart will help us identify the most common names in the dataset and their frequency.

goals.question: What is the distribution of heights for people with the same name?

goals.rationale: A box plot grouped by name will help us identify any differences in height distribution among people with the same name.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['height'])
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f} cm')
    plt.title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Height')
    plt.ylabel('Centimeters')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['age'], data['height'])
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between age and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    ax = name_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c')
    plt.title('What are the most common names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Names')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Name Frequency'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='name', y='height', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of heights for people with the same name?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Height (cm)')
    plt.legend(title='Name', loc='upper right', labels=data['name'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
